Share Proxmox Backups Locally with Samba
Log into Proxmox VE, either at the console or the web UI and launch the web shell
Run the following commands
# update software repositories
apt update
# install samba
apt install samba -y
# edit the samba conf file
nano /etc/samba/smb.conf
Paste the following at the bottom of the file
[vmbackups]
comment = Proxmox backups
path = /var/lib/vz
guest ok = no
public = yes
writable = yes

Press CTRL+O, Enter, CTRL+X to write the changes
Continue with the following commands
# restart samba service
systemctl restart smbd
Test that the new samba share is accessible, from Windows \\DNSorIP\vmbackups
When prompted, login with root and the Proxmox root password
 
